name: Build - 3
description: This poster series transforms architectural buildings  made with the current of brutalism by coloring.   Brutalism, also known as Brutalist architecture, is a style that emerged  in the 1950s and grew out of the early-20th century modernist movement.  Brutalist buildings are characterised by their massive, monolithic and 'blocky'  appearance with a rigid geometric style and large-scale use of poured concrete.
